                    "kind": "text",
                    "data": "Done. The change compiles cleanly.\n\nWhat changed in `server.py`:\n\n```python\n        from pyngrok import ngrok\n        NGROK_AUTHTOKEN = os.environ.get('NGROK_AUTHTOKEN')\n        if NGROK_AUTHTOKEN:\n            ngrok.set_auth_token(NGROK_AUTHTOKEN)\n        # Use the reserved/permanent domain from the ngrok account.\n        # Override with the NGROK_DOMAIN env var if needed.\n        NGROK_DOMAIN = os.environ.get('NGROK_DOMAIN', 'sijori.ngrok.dev')\n        public_url = ngrok.connect(8080, domain=NGROK_DOMAIN)\n        print(f\"\\nPublic URL: {public_url}\\n\")\n```\n\nThe tunnel now binds to your permanent domain `sijori.ngrok.dev` instead of a random URL. I made it overridable via the `NGROK_DOMAIN` env var, but it defaults to your domain so no extra config is needed.\n\nTwo things to note:\n- Reserved domains require auth, so `NGROK_AUTHTOKEN` must be set in your environment (the code already reads it). If it's missing, ngrok will reject the reserved domain with an auth error.\n- The public URL will be `https://sijori.ngrok.dev` forwarding to local port 8080."
                  }
